
[1]pietist

   PI'ETIST, n. One of a sect professing great strictness and purity of
   life, despising learning, school theology and ecclesiastical polity, as
   also forms and ceremonies in religion, and giving themselves up to
   mystic theology. This sect sprung up among the protestants of Germany,
   in the latter part of the seventeenth century.
